{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"In his inaugural address,"},{"time":2000,"text":"Barack Obama appealed to each of us to give our best"},{"time":6000,"text":"as we try to extricate ourselves from this current financial crisis."},{"time":12000,"text":"But what did he appeal to?"},{"time":14000,"text":"He did not, happily, follow in the footsteps of his predecessor,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and tell us to just go shopping."},{"time":22000,"text":"Nor did he tell us, \"Trust us. Trust your country."},{"time":26000,"text":"Invest, invest, invest.\""},{"time":30000,"text":"Instead, what he told us was to put aside childish things."},{"time":35000,"text":"And he appealed to virtue."},{"time":39000,"text":"Virtue is an old-fashioned word."},{"time":43000,"text":"It seems a little out of place in a cutting-edge environment like this one."},{"time":48000,"text":"And besides, some of you might be wondering,"},{"time":51000,"text":"what the hell does it mean?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"Let me begin with an example."},{"time":57000,"text":"This is the job description of a hospital janitor"},{"time":60000,"text":"that is scrolling up on the screen."},{"time":63000,"text":"And all of the items on it are unremarkable."},{"time":68000,"text":"They're the things you would expect:"},{"time":71000,"text":"mop the floors, sweep them, empty the trash, restock the cabinets."},{"time":76000,"text":"It may be a little surprising how many things there are,"},{"time":79000,"text":"but it's not surprising what they are."},{"time":81000,"text":"But the one thing I want you to notice about them is this:"},{"time":84000,"text":"even though this is a very long list,"},{"time":87000,"text":"there isn't a single thing on it that involves other human beings."},{"time":92000,"text":"Not one."},{"time":95000,"text":"The janitor's job could just as well be done in a mortuary as in a hospital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"And yet, when some psychologists interviewed hospital janitors"},{"time":105000,"text":"to get a sense of what they thought their jobs were like,"},{"time":108000,"text":"they encountered Mike,"},{"time":111000,"text":"who told them about how he stopped mopping the floor"},{"time":114000,"text":"because Mr. Jones was out of his bed getting a little exercise,"},{"time":117000,"text":"trying to build up his strength, walking slowly up and down the hall."},{"time":121000,"text":"And Charlene told them about how she ignored her supervisor's admonition"},{"time":127000,"text":"and didn't vacuum the visitor's lounge"},{"time":130000,"text":"because there were some family members who were there all day, every day"},{"time":133000,"text":"who, at this moment, happened to be taking a nap."},{"time":136000,"text":"And then there was Luke,"},{"time":138000,"text":"who washed the floor in a comatose young man's room twice"},{"time":142000,"text":"because the man's father, who had been keeping a vigil for six months,"},{"time":147000,"text":"didn't see Luke do it the first time,"},{"time":150000,"text":"and his father was angry."},{"time":152000,"text":"And behavior like this from janitors, from technicians, from nurses"},{"time":158000,"text":"and, if we're lucky now and then, from doctors,"},{"time":161000,"text":"doesn't just make people feel a little better,"},{"time":164000,"text":"it actually improves the quality of patient care"},{"time":167000,"text":"and enables hospitals to run well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"Now, not all janitors are like this, of course."},{"time":173000,"text":"But the ones who are think that these sorts of human interactions"},{"time":179000,"text":"involving kindness, care and empathy"},{"time":182000,"text":"are an essential part of the job."},{"time":184000,"text":"And yet their job description contains not one word about other human beings."},{"time":189000,"text":"These janitors have the moral will to do right by other people."},{"time":195000,"text":"And beyond this, they have the moral skill to figure out what \"doing right\" means."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202000,"text":"\"Practical wisdom,\" Aristotle told us,"},{"time":207000,"text":"\"is the combination of moral will and moral skill.\""},{"time":210000,"text":"A wise person knows when and how to make the exception to every rule,"},{"time":217000,"text":"as the janitors knew when to ignore the job duties in the service of other objectives."},{"time":223000,"text":"A wise person knows how to improvise,"},{"time":227000,"text":"as Luke did when he re-washed the floor."},{"time":230000,"text":"Real-world problems are often ambiguous and ill-defined"},{"time":233000,"text":"and the context is always changing."},{"time":236000,"text":"A wise person is like a jazz musician --"},{"time":239000,"text":"using the notes on the page, but dancing around them,"},{"time":242000,"text":"inventing combinations that are appropriate for the situation and the people at hand."},{"time":249000,"text":"A wise person knows how to use these moral skills"},{"time":252000,"text":"in the service of the right aims."},{"time":255000,"text":"To serve other people, not to manipulate other people."},{"time":259000,"text":"And finally, perhaps most important,"},{"time":262000,"text":"a wise person is made, not born."},{"time":265000,"text":"Wisdom depends on experience,"},{"time":268000,"text":"and not just any experience."},{"time":271000,"text":"You need the time to get to know the people that you're serving."},{"time":275000,"text":"You need permission to be allowed to improvise,"},{"time":278000,"text":"try new things, occasionally to fail and to learn from your failures."},{"time":283000,"text":"And you need to be mentored by wise teachers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"When you ask the janitors who behaved like the ones I described"},{"time":291000,"text":"how hard it is to learn to do their job,"},{"time":294000,"text":"they tell you that it takes lots of experience."},{"time":297000,"text":"And they don't mean it takes lots of experience to learn how to mop floors and empty trash cans."},{"time":301000,"text":"It takes lots of experience to learn how to care for people."},{"time":307000,"text":"At TED, brilliance is rampant."},{"time":311000,"text":"It's scary."},{"time":313000,"text":"The good news is you don't need to be brilliant to be wise."},{"time":318000,"text":"The bad news is that without wisdom,"},{"time":322000,"text":"brilliance isn't enough."},{"time":325000,"text":"It's as likely to get you and other people into trouble as anything else."},{"time":331000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"Now, I hope that we all know this."},{"time":337000,"text":"There's a sense in which it's obvious,"},{"time":340000,"text":"and yet, let me tell you a little story."},{"time":343000,"text":"It's a story about lemonade."},{"time":346000,"text":"A dad and his seven-year-old son were watching a Detroit Tigers game at the ballpark."},{"time":352000,"text":"His son asked him for some lemonade"},{"time":354000,"text":"and Dad went to the concession stand to buy it."},{"time":357000,"text":"All they had was Mike's Hard Lemonade,"},{"time":360000,"text":"which was five percent alcohol."},{"time":363000,"text":"Dad, being an academic, had no idea that Mike's Hard Lemonade contained alcohol."},{"time":369000,"text":"So he brought it back."},{"time":372000,"text":"And the kid was drinking it, and a security guard spotted it,"},{"time":375000,"text":"and called the police, who called an ambulance"},{"time":378000,"text":"that rushed to the ballpark, whisked the kid to the hospital."},{"time":381000,"text":"The emergency room ascertained that the kid had no alcohol in his blood."},{"time":385000,"text":"And they were ready to let the kid go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388000,"text":"But not so fast."},{"time":391000,"text":"The Wayne County Child Welfare Protection Agency said no."},{"time":395000,"text":"And the child was sent to a foster home for three days."},{"time":399000,"text":"At that point, can the child go home?"},{"time":402000,"text":"Well, a judge said yes, but only if the dad leaves the house and checks into a motel."},{"time":414000,"text":"After two weeks, I'm happy to report,"},{"time":417000,"text":"the family was reunited."},{"time":419000,"text":"But the welfare workers and the ambulance people"},{"time":422000,"text":"and the judge all said the same thing:"},{"time":425000,"text":"\"We hate to do it but we have to follow procedure.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"How do things like this happen?"},{"time":433000,"text":"Scott Simon, who told this story on NPR,"},{"time":437000,"text":"said, \"Rules and procedures may be dumb,"},{"time":441000,"text":"but they spare you from thinking.\""},{"time":444000,"text":"And, to be fair, rules are often imposed"},{"time":446000,"text":"because previous officials have been lax"},{"time":449000,"text":"and they let a child go back to an abusive household."},{"time":452000,"text":"Fair enough."},{"time":453000,"text":"When things go wrong, as of course they do,"},{"time":456000,"text":"we reach for two tools to try to fix them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460000,"text":"One tool we reach for is rules."},{"time":463000,"text":"Better ones, more of them."},{"time":466000,"text":"The second tool we reach for is incentives."},{"time":469000,"text":"Better ones, more of them."},{"time":472000,"text":"What else, after all, is there?"},{"time":475000,"text":"We can certainly see this in response to the current financial crisis."},{"time":480000,"text":"Regulate, regulate, regulate."},{"time":483000,"text":"Fix the incentives, fix the incentives, fix the incentives ..."},{"time":486000,"text":"The truth is that neither rules nor incentives"},{"time":489000,"text":"are enough to do the job."},{"time":491000,"text":"How could you even write a rule that got the janitors to do what they did?"},{"time":495000,"text":"And would you pay them a bonus for being empathic?"},{"time":498000,"text":"It's preposterous on its face."},{"time":502000,"text":"And what happens is that as we turn increasingly to rules,"},{"time":507000,"text":"rules and incentives may make things better in the short run,"},{"time":511000,"text":"but they create a downward spiral"},{"time":514000,"text":"that makes them worse in the long run."},{"time":516000,"text":"Moral skill is chipped away by an over-reliance on rules"},{"time":521000,"text":"that deprives us of the opportunity"},{"time":523000,"text":"to improvise and learn from our improvisations."},{"time":526000,"text":"And moral will is undermined"},{"time":529000,"text":"by an incessant appeal to incentives"},{"time":532000,"text":"that destroy our desire to do the right thing."},{"time":535000,"text":"And without intending it,"},{"time":537000,"text":"by appealing to rules and incentives,"},{"time":541000,"text":"we are engaging in a war on wisdom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543000,"text":"Let me just give you a few examples,"},{"time":546000,"text":"first of rules and the war on moral skill."},{"time":549000,"text":"The lemonade story is one."},{"time":551000,"text":"Second, no doubt more familiar to you,"},{"time":554000,"text":"is the nature of modern American education:"},{"time":557000,"text":"scripted, lock-step curricula."},{"time":560000,"text":"Here's an example from Chicago kindergarten."},{"time":563000,"text":"Reading and enjoying literature"},{"time":565000,"text":"and words that begin with 'B.'"},{"time":567000,"text":"\"The Bath:\" Assemble students on a rug"},{"time":570000,"text":"and give students a warning about the dangers of hot water."},{"time":572000,"text":"Say 75 items in this script to teach a 25-page picture book."},{"time":577000,"text":"All over Chicago in every kindergarten class in the city,"},{"time":580000,"text":"every teacher is saying the same words in the same way on the same day."},{"time":587000,"text":"We know why these scripts are there."},{"time":591000,"text":"We don't trust the judgment of teachers enough"},{"time":594000,"text":"to let them loose on their own."},{"time":597000,"text":"Scripts like these are insurance policies against disaster."},{"time":600000,"text":"And they prevent disaster."},{"time":603000,"text":"But what they assure in its place is mediocrity."},{"time":608000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":615000,"text":"Don't get me wrong. We need rules!"},{"time":617000,"text":"Jazz musicians need some notes --"},{"time":619000,"text":"most of them need some notes on the page."},{"time":621000,"text":"We need more rules for the bankers, God knows."},{"time":623000,"text":"But too many rules prevent accomplished jazz musicians"},{"time":627000,"text":"from improvising."},{"time":629000,"text":"And as a result, they lose their gifts,"},{"time":632000,"text":"or worse, they stop playing altogether."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"Now, how about incentives?"},{"time":638000,"text":"They seem cleverer."},{"time":640000,"text":"If you have one reason for doing something"},{"time":642000,"text":"and I give you a second reason for doing the same thing,"},{"time":645000,"text":"it seems only logical that two reasons are better than one"},{"time":648000,"text":"and you're more likely to do it."},{"time":651000,"text":"Right?"},{"time":653000,"text":"Well, not always."},{"time":655000,"text":"Sometimes two reasons to do the same thing seem to compete with one another"},{"time":658000,"text":"instead of complimenting,"},{"time":660000,"text":"and they make people less likely to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"I'll just give you one example because time is racing."},{"time":666000,"text":"In Switzerland, back about 15 years ago,"},{"time":669000,"text":"they were trying to decide where to site nuclear waste dumps."},{"time":672000,"text":"There was going to be a national referendum."},{"time":675000,"text":"Some psychologists went around and polled citizens who were very well informed."},{"time":678000,"text":"And they said, \"Would you be willing to have a nuclear waste dump in your community?\""},{"time":681000,"text":"Astonishingly, 50 percent of the citizens said yes."},{"time":686000,"text":"They knew it was dangerous."},{"time":688000,"text":"They thought it would reduce their property values."},{"time":691000,"text":"But it had to go somewhere"},{"time":694000,"text":"and they had responsibilities as citizens."},{"time":697000,"text":"The psychologists asked other people a slightly different question."},{"time":701000,"text":"They said, \"If we paid you six weeks' salary every year"},{"time":704000,"text":"would you be willing to have a nuclear waste dump in your community?\""},{"time":708000,"text":"Two reasons. It's my responsibility and I'm getting paid."},{"time":712000,"text":"Instead of 50 percent saying yes,"},{"time":715000,"text":"25 percent said yes."},{"time":718000,"text":"What happens is that"},{"time":721000,"text":"the second this introduction of incentive gets us"},{"time":725000,"text":"so that instead of asking, \"What is my responsibility?\""},{"time":728000,"text":"all we ask is, \"What serves my interests?\""},{"time":731000,"text":"When incentives don't work,"},{"time":733000,"text":"when CEOs ignore the long-term health of their companies"},{"time":736000,"text":"in pursuit of short-term gains that will lead to massive bonuses,"},{"time":740000,"text":"the response is always the same."},{"time":744000,"text":"Get smarter incentives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748000,"text":"The truth is that there are no incentives that you can devise"},{"time":751000,"text":"that are ever going to be smart enough."},{"time":754000,"text":"Any incentive system can be subverted by bad will."},{"time":758000,"text":"We need incentives. People have to make a living."},{"time":762000,"text":"But excessive reliance on incentives"},{"time":764000,"text":"demoralizes professional activity"},{"time":767000,"text":"in two senses of that word."},{"time":770000,"text":"It causes people who engage in that activity to lose morale"},{"time":774000,"text":"and it causes the activity itself to lose morality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778000,"text":"Barack Obama said, before he was inaugurated,"},{"time":783000,"text":"\"We must ask not just 'Is it profitable?' but 'Is it right?'\""},{"time":787000,"text":"And when professions are demoralized,"},{"time":790000,"text":"everyone in them becomes dependent on -- addicted to -- incentives"},{"time":795000,"text":"and they stop asking \"Is it right?\""},{"time":798000,"text":"We see this in medicine."},{"time":801000,"text":"(\"Although it's nothing serious, let's keep an eye on it to make sure it doesn't turn into a major lawsuit.\")"},{"time":805000,"text":"And we certainly see it in the world of business."},{"time":807000,"text":"(\"In order to remain competitive in today's marketplace, I'm afraid we're going to have to replace you with a sleezeball.\")"},{"time":813000,"text":"(\"I sold my soul for about a tenth of what the damn things are going for now.\")"},{"time":818000,"text":"It is obvious that this is not the way people want to do their work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821000,"text":"So what can we do?"},{"time":824000,"text":"A few sources of hope:"},{"time":827000,"text":"we ought to try to re-moralize work."},{"time":830000,"text":"One way not to do it: teach more ethics courses."},{"time":836000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":839000,"text":"There is no better way to show people that you're not serious"},{"time":842000,"text":"than to tie up everything you have to say about ethics"},{"time":845000,"text":"into a little package with a bow and consign it to the margins as an ethics course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850000,"text":"What to do instead?"},{"time":852000,"text":"One: Celebrate moral exemplars."},{"time":856000,"text":"Acknowledge, when you go to law school,"},{"time":859000,"text":"that a little voice is whispering in your ear"},{"time":862000,"text":"about Atticus Finch."},{"time":865000,"text":"No 10-year-old goes to law school to do mergers and acquisitions."},{"time":868000,"text":"People are inspired by moral heroes."},{"time":871000,"text":"But we learn that with sophistication"},{"time":874000,"text":"comes the understanding that you can't acknowledge that you have moral heroes."},{"time":878000,"text":"Well, acknowledge them."},{"time":880000,"text":"Be proud that you have them."},{"time":882000,"text":"Celebrate them."},{"time":884000,"text":"And demand that the people who teach you acknowledge them and celebrate them too."},{"time":887000,"text":"That's one thing we can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890000,"text":"I don't know how many of you remember this:"},{"time":893000,"text":"another moral hero, 15 years ago, Aaron Feuerstein,"},{"time":897000,"text":"who was the head of Malden Mills in Massachusetts --"},{"time":900000,"text":"they made Polartec --"},{"time":902000,"text":"The factory burned down."},{"time":904000,"text":"3,000 employees. He kept every one of them on the payroll."},{"time":907000,"text":"Why? Because it would have been a disaster for them"},{"time":910000,"text":"and for the community if he had let them go."},{"time":913000,"text":"\"Maybe on paper our company is worth less to Wall Street,"},{"time":917000,"text":"but I can tell you it's worth more. We're doing fine.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":921000,"text":"Just at this TED we heard talks from several moral heroes."},{"time":925000,"text":"Two were particularly inspiring to me."},{"time":928000,"text":"One was Ray Anderson, who turned --"},{"time":931000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":934000,"text":"-- turned, you know, a part of the evil empire"},{"time":937000,"text":"into a zero-footprint, or almost zero-footprint business."},{"time":940000,"text":"Why? Because it was the right thing to do."},{"time":944000,"text":"And a bonus he's discovering is"},{"time":947000,"text":"he's actually going to make even more money."},{"time":950000,"text":"His employees are inspired by the effort."},{"time":953000,"text":"Why? Because there happy to be doing something that's the right thing to do."},{"time":957000,"text":"Yesterday we heard Willie Smits talk about re-foresting in Indonesia."},{"time":962000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":965000,"text":"In many ways this is the perfect example."},{"time":968000,"text":"Because it took the will to do the right thing."},{"time":971000,"text":"God knows it took a huge amount of technical skill."},{"time":974000,"text":"I'm boggled at how much he and his associates needed to know"},{"time":977000,"text":"in order to plot this out."},{"time":980000,"text":"But most important to make it work --"},{"time":983000,"text":"and he emphasized this --"},{"time":985000,"text":"is that it took knowing the people in the communities."},{"time":988000,"text":"Unless the people you're working with are behind you,"},{"time":993000,"text":"this will fail."},{"time":995000,"text":"And there isn't a formula to tell you how to get the people behind you,"},{"time":998000,"text":"because different people in different communities"},{"time":1001000,"text":"organize their lives in different ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004000,"text":"So there's a lot here at TED, and at other places, to celebrate."},{"time":1007000,"text":"And you don't have to be a mega-hero."},{"time":1010000,"text":"There are ordinary heroes."},{"time":1012000,"text":"Ordinary heroes like the janitors who are worth celebrating too."},{"time":1015000,"text":"As practitioners each and every one of us should strive"},{"time":1018000,"text":"to be ordinary, if not extraordinary heroes."},{"time":1021000,"text":"As heads of organizations,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"we should strive to create environments"},{"time":1025000,"text":"that encourage and nurture both moral skill and moral will."},{"time":1030000,"text":"Even the wisest and most well-meaning people"},{"time":1033000,"text":"will give up if they have to swim against the current"},{"time":1036000,"text":"in the organizations in which they work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039000,"text":"If you run an organization, you should be sure"},{"time":1042000,"text":"that none of the jobs -- none of the jobs --"},{"time":1045000,"text":"have job descriptions like the job descriptions of the janitors."},{"time":1048000,"text":"Because the truth is that"},{"time":1051000,"text":"any work that you do that involves interaction with other people"},{"time":1054000,"text":"is moral work."},{"time":1057000,"text":"And any moral work depends upon practical wisdom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1061000,"text":"And, perhaps most important,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"as teachers, we should strive to be the ordinary heroes,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"the moral exemplars, to the people we mentor."},{"time":1071000,"text":"And there are a few things that we have to remember as teachers."},{"time":1074000,"text":"One is that we are always teaching."},{"time":1078000,"text":"Someone is always watching."},{"time":1081000,"text":"The camera is always on."},{"time":1083000,"text":"Bill Gates talked about the importance of education"},{"time":1086000,"text":"and, in particular, the model that KIPP was providing:"},{"time":1089000,"text":"\"Knowledge is power.\""},{"time":1092000,"text":"And he talked about a lot of the wonderful things"},{"time":1095000,"text":"that KIPP is doing"},{"time":1097000,"text":"to take inner-city kids and turn them in the direction of college."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101000,"text":"I want to focus on one particular thing KIPP is doing"},{"time":1104000,"text":"that Bill didn't mention."},{"time":1107000,"text":"That is that they have come to the realization"},{"time":1110000,"text":"that the single most important thing kids need to learn"},{"time":1112000,"text":"is character."},{"time":1113000,"text":"They need to learn to respect themselves."},{"time":1116000,"text":"They need to learn to respect their schoolmates."},{"time":1119000,"text":"They need to learn to respect their teachers."},{"time":1122000,"text":"And, most important, they need to learn to respect learning."},{"time":1125000,"text":"That's the principle objective."},{"time":1127000,"text":"If you do that, the rest is just pretty much a coast downhill."},{"time":1131000,"text":"And the teachers: the way you teach these things to the kids"},{"time":1134000,"text":"is by having the teachers and all the other staff embody it every minute of every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1141000,"text":"Obama appealed to virtue."},{"time":1143000,"text":"And I think he was right."},{"time":1145000,"text":"And the virtue I think we need above all others is practical wisdom,"},{"time":1149000,"text":"because it's what allows other virtues -- honesty, kindness, courage and so on --"},{"time":1156000,"text":"to be displayed at the right time and in the right way."},{"time":1159000,"text":"He also appealed to hope."},{"time":1162000,"text":"Right again."},{"time":1164000,"text":"I think there is reason for hope."},{"time":1167000,"text":"I think people want to be allowed to be virtuous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1170000,"text":"In many ways, it's what TED is all about."},{"time":1174000,"text":"Wanting to do the right thing"},{"time":1177000,"text":"in the right way"},{"time":1179000,"text":"for the right reasons."},{"time":1181000,"text":"This kind of wisdom is within the grasp of each and every one of us"},{"time":1184000,"text":"if only we start paying attention."},{"time":1187000,"text":"Paying attention to what we do,"},{"time":1190000,"text":"to how we do it,"},{"time":1192000,"text":"and, perhaps most importantly,"},{"time":1194000,"text":"to the structure of the organizations within which we work,"},{"time":1197000,"text":"so as to make sure that it enables us and other people to develop wisdom"},{"time":1202000,"text":"rather than having it suppressed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1205000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1208000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1210000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1213000,"text":"Chris Anderson: You have to go and stand out here a sec."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1219000,"text":"Barry Schwartz: Thank you very much."},{"time":1221000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}